fication on Planes Raid Signups - Please Read</span><hr size=1> I just want to make doubly sure that everyone who signs up for a Council of Guilds planes raid (whether it be led by Zellex, Jzonn or whoever) must be from a guild that is either not able to do the planes on its own, or is not in a guild. The only exceptions to this are those that the raid organizer designates as his management body. <br><br>This means that those of you whose guilds are already doing planes, please do not sign up. And I don't just mean those whose guilds do the planes by themselves, but also those guilds who are part of multi-guild alliances that currently do the planes. Unless you are an invited member of the management body, the KGC guidelines on scheduling of planes raids discourage having visitors from other guilds already in the rotation. I appreciate the help you are giving to the CoG raids, but we follow the KGC scheduling guidelines in the interest of peaceful sharing of these large targets. <br><br>Haemish MacLennan<br>Clan Chieftan<br>The Silver Daggers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uedinaelvander.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edina Elvander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/1/00 8:39:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RE:  Raid Sign-Ups</span><hr size=1> I want to make sure I understand this.  If my guild, Haven of Light, belongs to another alliance that is also in the plane/dragon rotation then our members cannot attend a plane/dragon raid with CoG?<br><br>We have many members that, because of RL schedules, can't make the raids with the other alliance on their specified dates.  Another alliance gives us the chance to participate.  What if the other alliance we belong to has the same rule?<br><br>By limiting participants, you eliminate possibly needed classes.  For instance the last dragon raid, was a no go because the mix of classes wasn't right.  Also, as a reminder, I and six guildmates showed up for a Nagafen raid and no one else did.  We were ready to fight for the alliance.<br><br>CoG could be passing on more raids because of these limitations.<br><br><br>Thank you,<br>Edina Elvander<br>Haven of Light<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uedinaelvander.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edina Elvander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/1/00 8:54:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Raid Sign-ups</span><hr size=1> Well, I just finished reading the plane raid re-cap posts.  I apologize.  I thought this was a recent decision.  I assumed that since we were a member of the alliance, we were entitled to attend all alliance functions which included raids.  I will go back to the KGC guildlines to review them.  <br><br>I have attended 2 dragon raids with CoG, so I am in violation of the guildlines.  My apologies to alliance.  It will not happen again.  I will inform my guild of this rule.  I am saddened we cannot attend any raids with CoG.<br><br>I wish you the best of luck in all future raids.<br><br>Edina<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/2/00 12:10:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Raid Sign-ups</span><hr size=1> Actually, upon further re-reading of the guidelines, a tempest in a teapot was created. The only prohibition made on guests are for GOD size targets, not planes raids. Disregard this post, and as a matter of fact I might just have to delete it. <br><br>I apologize if I've offended anyone, I just want to make sure that the CoG isn't seen by anyone as trying to make special exceptions for it in planes raids. As the rule that I mention above does NOT violate any KGC guidelines, all are free to attend. <br><br>Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uplangstrump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>P Langstrump</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/2/00 5:00:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/seyil/villa/pippirun.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Raid Sign-ups</span><hr size=1> erm, just to clarify (and I think I am right here) - the CoG is NOT an alliance. We are just a group of people, regardless of guild, who like to organize and sponsor server-wide events and mingle across guilds.  Of course, there may be alliances within the participants and volunteers of the CoG since the CoG is there for anyone on the server.<br><br>Whatever restrictions are currently in place is imposed by KGC and alliances, not us - we are merely adhering to their requests / standards. <br><br>Hope this clarifies it.<br>Pippi <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uplangstrump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>P Langstrump</A> at: 12/2/00 5:03:16 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uedinaelvander.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edina Elvander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/2/00 6:10:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RE:  Raid Sign-ups</span><hr size=1> Thank you very much for clarifying this issue.  See you soon!<br><br>Edina <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/2/00 10:57:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:  Raid Sign-ups</span><hr size=1> I'm actually going to leave this topic up here, so that people can read what was discussed, and know that there are no restrictions on people joining in on CoG planes raids. <br><br>And Pippi is right, we aren't an alliance, have no ruling body, and only do what we do through the efforts of those guilds who volunteer to run events, such as Zellex and the Watchmen hosting our planes raids. The more who volunteer, the more we do!<br><br>Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showPrevMessage?topicID=57.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showNextMessage?topicID=57.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.emailToFriend?topicID=57.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.threadControl?topicID=57.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=57.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=57.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub6.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="councilofguildsgeneral">General